## 3  Inferential Statistics: Substrate Cover Between Sites

> **Addresses**: R2.23, R2.24, R1.9, R2.28, R2.39 — all claims of spatial heterogeneity must be statistically supported.

### 3.1  Kruskal–Wallis + Dunn post-hoc: coral cover

```{r kw-coral}
#| label: kw-coral

# Non-parametric (proportion data, likely non-normal) → Kruskal-Wallis
kw_coral <- substrate_clean |> kruskal_test(coral_pct ~ dive_site)
print(kw_coral)

dunn_coral <- substrate_clean |>
  dunn_test(coral_pct ~ dive_site, p.adjust.method = "BH") |>
  add_significance()
print(dunn_coral)

# Compact letter display for boxplot annotation
pv_coral <- setNames(dunn_coral$p.adj,
                     paste(dunn_coral$group1, dunn_coral$group2, sep = "-"))
letters_coral <- multcompLetters(pv_coral)$Letters
letters_coral_df <- data.frame(
  dive_site = factor(names(letters_coral), levels = site_levels),
  letter    = letters_coral,
  y_pos     = max(substrate_clean$coral_pct, na.rm = TRUE) * 1.08
)
cat("\nCompact letter display (coral cover, BH-adjusted Dunn test):\n")
print(letters_coral_df)
```

